The White House Office of the Press Secretary released a fact sheet outlining the U.S. government's support for democratic institutions, good governance, and human rights in Africa. The United States is committed to helping African countries strengthen their political institutions, address governance challenges, promote civil society, and uphold human rights. This support is seen as vital for achieving Africa's economic and security goals. The U.S. government's efforts include supporting free and fair elections, promoting civil society and civic engagement, partnering to promote good governance and openness, and consolidating the rule of law and protecting human rights. These efforts involve providing financial assistance, training, and capacity building to African countries in areas such as election support, civil society empowerment, government accountability, and human rights protection.